abstract:

Speaker:: Tanmoy Bandyopadhyay Track: PyCon: Libraries IPC and Synchronization techniques using Python will be explained in this tutorial. We will learn how to pass messages to processes using Queue and Pipes, share data between processes using Shared Memory, effectively use Synchronization Primitives like Lock, Event, Condition and Semaphore. Recorded at the PyConDE & PyData Berlin 2022 conference, April 11-13 2022. https://2022.pycon.de More details at the conference page: https://2022.pycon.de/program/VCTPVE Twitter: https://twitter.com/pydataberlin Twitter: https://twitter.com/pyconde
---
full_description:

Speaker:: Tanmoy Bandyopadhyay

Track: PyCon: Libraries
IPC and Synchronization techniques using Python will be explained in this tutorial. We will 
learn how to pass messages to processes using Queue and Pipes, share data between processes 
using Shared Memory, effectively use Synchronization Primitives like Lock, Event, Condition 
and Semaphore.


Recorded at the PyConDE & PyData Berlin 2022 conference, April 11-13 2022.
https://2022.pycon.de
More details at the conference page: https://2022.pycon.de/program/VCTPVE
Twitter: https://twitter.com/pydataberlin
Twitter: https://twitter.com/pyconde
